00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:59,630
but his eyes said he was on your side.

264
00:17:01,310 --> 00:17:03,120
 I did it all for you. 

265
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:06,140
 I did it all for you, I said! 

266
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:10,190
Anyway, make up your mind between Choi Se Kyeong and Ha Eun Gyeol.

267
00:17:10,190 --> 00:17:14,630
By the way, if Ha Eun Gyeol leaves, I'll leave, too.

268
00:17:14,630 --> 00:17:16,280
What?

269
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:22,970
♪  Now I know what it feels like to be alone  ♪

270
00:17:22,970 --> 00:17:26,110
♪  I was mistaken  ♪

271
00:17:26,110 --> 00:17:28,030
♪  Can you feel it?  ♪

272
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:33,480
♪  The beginning of love is the end of loneliness  ♪

273
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:35,200
♪  Now I know  ♪

274
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,980
Cheong Ah. Yoon Cheong Ah!

275
00:17:39,890 --> 00:17:42,280
Why do you keep acting like this?

276
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,820
Why are you like this?

277
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:46,220
Tell me what I did wrong—

278
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:49,480
Cheong Ah.

279
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:53,040
Cheong Ah. Yoon Cheong Ah.

280
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:58,530
You have serious separation anxiety.

281
00:17:58,530 --> 00:18:01,500
Bark! Bark! Are you a dog? Do you like all humans?

282
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,500
You don't care if it's a man or a woman?

283
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:06,580
I think you're mistaken. Cheong Ah and I aren't like that—

284
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:07,730
Of course not.

285
00:18:07,730 --> 00:18:09,510
Follow me. We need to go somewhere.

286
00:18:09,510 --> 00:18:11,850
I'm sorry, but I have a bit of a situation today.

287
00:18:11,850 --> 00:18:15,690
Is that so? I should go see Lee Chan, then.

288
00:18:15,690 --> 00:18:17,410
Lee Chan?

289
00:18:17,410 --> 00:18:19,060
Hey.

290
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:29,780
Why are you so obsessed with feeding this to me?

291
00:18:29,780 --> 00:18:30,770
You said you like me.

292
00:18:30,770 --> 00:18:34,450
What does that have to do with this capsaicin-rich thing?

293
00:18:34,450 --> 00:18:38,180
Did I ask you to get me a star? Did I insist on getting buried with you?

294
00:18:38,180 --> 00:18:41,240
You can't even eat some pig trotters with me?

295
00:18:43,310 --> 00:18:45,460
What? Don't you want it?

296
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:47,030
You can't eat it because it's too spicy?

297
00:18:47,030 --> 00:18:49,400
How would you like me to eat it?

298
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,420
What?

299
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:53,250
You said your life depends on this, and it's important.

300
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:56,540
I can tell you aren't just joking.

301
00:18:56,540 --> 00:19:01,450
I can't ignore someone's desperate situation because it looks trivial to me.

302
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:06,160
I know what it's like to be in a situation you can't talk about.

303
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:10,720
How would you like me to eat it?

304
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:13,430
Do you want me to eat it well or not be able to eat it?

305
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:16,860
I'll try my best to do what you want.

306
00:19:17,540 --> 00:19:19,400
Eat it well.

307
00:19:20,770 --> 00:19:24,430
That's not what I meant. Not be able...

308
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:28,790
No, I mean... Eat well... No...

309
00:19:28,790 --> 00:19:31,790
Dang it. I don't know. Do whatever you want.

310
00:19:31,790 --> 00:19:34,530
Okay. I'll do whatever I want.

311
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,360
Hold it!

312
00:19:48,550 --> 00:19:49,800
Don't...

313
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:52,550
Don't eat it just yet. Okay?

314
00:19:52,550 --> 00:19:56,290
Ma'am, we'll have this to go. To go.

315
00:20:02,550 --> 00:20:03,760
Excuse me.

316
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:05,900
What? What is it? What?

317
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:08,530
When can I hear your answer, by the way?

318
00:20:08,530 --> 00:20:09,930
Answer?

319
00:20:09,930 --> 00:20:11,920
What answer?

320
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:16,870
The answer to my confession.

321
00:20:18,850 --> 00:20:21,750
I'd like to know what you think of me.

322
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:26,990
There used to be a handsome and cute puppy in my neighborhood.

323
00:20:26,990 --> 00:20:31,990
It was a mix between Shiba Inu and Siberian Husky. 
    

324
00:20:31,990 --> 00:20:33,950
And? 
    

325
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,230
He looked like you.

326
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:38,410
What do you mean by that?

327
00:20:38,410 --> 00:20:40,240
Do you mean I'm cute or handsome—

328
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:41,830
Shiba-sky. 
  (Sounds like a swear word in Korean) 

329
00:20:41,830 --> 00:20:46,360
- Shiba? 
 - You're no more or less than Shiba-sky.

330
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:48,150
So just wait.

331
00:20:48,150 --> 00:20:53,430
Until I decide if I'll give you a treat or not.

332
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,420
This is too difficult.

333
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:59,850
I have no idea what she's saying.

334
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:02,930
Shiba-sky? Did she swear at me?

335
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:11,220
What's with you, On Eun Yoo?

336
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:14,540
Why did you hesitate instead of just checking that...

337
00:21:18,010 --> 00:21:22,010
But wait. Isn't spice tolerance relative?

338
00:21:22,010 --> 00:21:24,740
Who sets the standard? How tolerant are you supposed to be?

339
00:21:24,740 --> 00:21:29,420
Shouldn't I include Hyeon Yool, who ate the spicy chicken feet like nothing, then?

340
00:21:31,140 --> 00:21:34,890
Gosh, seriously. Why did Mom give me such a sucky hint?

341
00:21:34,890 --> 00:21:36,240
Gosh.

342
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:39,740
 I was sure it was him then. 

343
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:42,990
- When? 
  - During the spring festival. 

344
00:21:42,990 --> 00:21:48,270
 He serenaded me on stage that day. 

345
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:53,240
 I heard you guys ask whether you were struck by someone or he grew on you these days. 

346
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:56,600
 I think he grew on me. 

347
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:59,630
 Slowly, like getting wet in light rain. 

348
00:22:00,690 --> 00:22:03,220
 And it struck me that day. 

349
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:07,850
 I thought, "I like this person. 

350
00:22:07,850 --> 00:22:11,710
 Or maybe I've been liking him this whole time. 

351
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:16,050
 There must be no way out anymore." 

352
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:19,410
 It was kind of like getting struck by lightning. 

353
00:22:19,410 --> 00:22:23,450
Yes. I wasn't being swayed by Ha Eun Gyeol.

354
00:22:23,450 --> 00:22:27,510
A more clear clue was in my memory.

355
00:22:27,510 --> 00:22:30,380
That's it. Between Ha Lee Chan and Ha Eun Gyeol,

356
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:33,340
whoever serenades Mom is her first love

357
00:22:33,340 --> 00:22:37,640
and I just need to be open-minded and observe them until then.

358
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:40,680
I'll be secretive and fair.

359
00:22:42,660 --> 00:22:44,400
Let's start the lesson.

360
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:48,630
What are you doing? What are you doing?

361
00:22:48,630 --> 00:22:52,820
I just said, "Let's start the lesson." Why are you angry?

362
00:22:57,490 --> 00:23:01,500
Why are both Mom and Dad doing this to me?

363
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:03,930
What did I do, anyway?

364
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:10,580
   

365
00:23:10,580 --> 00:23:12,730
   

366
00:23:12,730 --> 00:23:14,230
   

367
00:23:14,770 --> 00:23:16,170
 By chance... 

368
00:23:16,170 --> 00:23:18,750
   

369
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:21,420
 No way! 

370
00:23:21,420 --> 00:23:23,360
   

371
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,520
   

372
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:27,540
 Heart symbol? 

373
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:33,860
By chance...

374
00:23:33,860 --> 00:23:36,440
do you like Ha Lee Chan, Mom?

375
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:42,580
Hold on, hold on. Let me ask you one thing. Just one thing!

376
00:23:47,770 --> 00:23:50,020
 Mom, I'll ask you just one thing. 

377
00:23:50,020 --> 00:23:52,760
Just this one thing!

378
00:23:55,070 --> 00:23:57,940
Mom had a crush on Dad.

379
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,460
I would've made a different plan if I knew.

380
00:24:02,460 --> 00:24:05,940
I shouldn't have provoked Dad.

381
00:24:05,940 --> 00:24:08,100
It's all ruined.

382
00:24:15,850 --> 00:24:21,620
   

383
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,360
You came.

384
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:48,110
Don't be intimidated and have a seat.

385
00:24:48,110 --> 00:24:50,520
I'm not interested in killing you yet.

386
00:24:57,750 --> 00:25:02,470
Why are you opening that? You said it was just a prop to intimidate him.

387
00:25:02,470 --> 00:25:05,450
Geez, it's open.

388
00:25:07,250 --> 00:25:08,490
Are you a choir?

389
00:25:08,490 --> 00:25:11,410
What are you standing there for?

390
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:17,080
- Sir. 
 - What?

391
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,440
I'll have a large jjajangmyeon.

392
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:21,540
One large jjajangmyeon? I'm angry.

393
00:25:21,540 --> 00:25:24,500
How annoying.

394
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:05,440
I've been thinking all night.

395
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:08,790
All the strange behavior you've been displaying

396
00:26:08,790 --> 00:26:14,230
suddenly made sense when you said you like Se Kyeong.

397
00:26:14,230 --> 00:26:17,280
I'm sorry about that.

398
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:20,340
I'll try to put myself in your socks and—

399
00:26:20,340 --> 00:26:22,590
You mean shoes. Geez...

400
00:26:22,590 --> 00:26:23,760
Shut up.

401
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:28,000
- I'll stitch up your mouth! 
 - Hey, hey, hey! Sit down.

402
00:26:30,930 --> 00:26:35,250
Yes. Socks or shoes, I'll just...

403
00:26:37,340 --> 00:26:40,950
Anyway, I'll make you an offer you can't refuse.

404
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:42,990
An offer? What offer?

405
00:26:42,990 --> 00:26:47,300
I won't tell you not to see Se Kyeong.

406
00:26:47,300 --> 00:26:50,760
So, you'd better not BS me saying not to see her, either.

407
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:52,390
Let's call a truce

408
00:26:52,390 --> 00:26:56,390
and just focus on the band until the festival. Deal?

409
00:26:56,390 --> 00:26:58,930
 This is an opportunity. How do I seize it? 

410
00:26:58,930 --> 00:27:01,730
You don't want to? You don't think you can?

411
00:27:01,730 --> 00:27:05,040
- Forget about it, then. 
 - What if we don't see her at all?

412
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:08,930
Neither of us will see Choi Se Kyeong until the festival. That's fair.

413
00:27:08,930 --> 00:27:14,050
Instead, we'll compete with each other on stage.

414
00:27:14,050 --> 00:27:15,430
What do you say?

415
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:25,220
You don't know how much I improved while you were gone, do you?

416
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:26,720
Am I the only one out of the loop?

417
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:31,490
Well, the ball is in Choi Se Kyeong's court already.

418
00:27:31,490 --> 00:27:35,700
She agreed to make a decision after seeing the performance, anyway.

419
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:38,150
- Lee Chan has nothing to lose. 
 - You heard that. Right?

420
00:27:38,150 --> 00:27:41,980
I'd be sad not seeing her for now,

421
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:44,630
but you'd be losing a lot. Would you be okay?

422
00:27:44,630 --> 00:27:48,350
Wow, what kind of calculator gives you that kind of answer?

423
00:27:48,350 --> 00:27:49,860
So?

424
00:27:49,860 --> 00:27:52,350
- Deal? 
 - Of course.

425
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:54,240
Deal!

426
00:27:56,290 --> 00:27:58,590
 He took the bait. 

427
00:27:58,590 --> 00:28:03,090
   

428
00:28:03,090 --> 00:28:06,530
As you know, we don't have a lot of time until the festival.

429
00:28:06,530 --> 00:28:10,500
But after the rain, the soil gets more... Whatever. We can do it.

430
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:14,020
- Let's go. 
 - Let's say "Fighting" together, then.

431
00:28:16,140 --> 00:28:18,220
Why are there only two hands?

432
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:22,250
Seriously. Hey!

433
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:29,720
Forget it, then.

434
00:28:32,430 --> 00:28:35,100
I heard you're the resident tutor for the Jinsung family.

435
00:28:35,800 --> 00:28:37,380
Why are you surprised?

436
00:28:37,380 --> 00:28:39,300
Don't you know rumors travel fast?

437
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:40,950
I've heard about it, too.

438
00:28:40,950 --> 00:28:43,290
So the thing is...

439
00:28:43,290 --> 00:28:46,170
the chairman of Jinsung Instruments is sponsoring me by chance—

440
00:28:46,170 --> 00:28:47,570
Whatever.

441
00:28:47,570 --> 00:28:51,300
It's better to get paid more from a rich family and teach a well-behaved student.

442
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:53,250
Go now. Bye.

443
00:28:53,250 --> 00:28:55,530
Is your grandmother doing well?

444
00:28:59,780 --> 00:29:03,580
Goodness, goodness. Welcome, Teacher.

445
00:29:03,580 --> 00:29:05,920
Goodness, I missed you.

446
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:07,690
Welcome, sir.

447
00:29:07,690 --> 00:29:09,380
Have you been doing well?

448
00:29:09,380 --> 00:29:11,780
I have, thanks to you.

449
00:29:11,780 --> 00:29:15,800
Come on. You should've told me he was coming.

450
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:18,150
I didn't make enough food. Not enough at all.

451
00:29:18,150 --> 00:29:22,220
He lived with us until recently. You don't have to prove your cooking skills.

452
00:29:22,220 --> 00:29:27,580
You didn't even give me a chance to do that. Gosh...

453
00:29:27,580 --> 00:29:29,740
Go inside. Go inside. Hurry in.

454
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:32,510
My, my, my. Take me inside, too!

455
00:29:32,510 --> 00:29:35,540
 It tastes pretty good. 

456
00:29:40,770 --> 00:29:42,850
Goodness.

457
00:29:42,850 --> 00:29:46,260
Gosh, I'm sorry there isn't much food.

458
00:29:46,260 --> 00:29:48,230
That family treats you well, right?

459
00:29:48,230 --> 00:29:50,150
I heard they're very wealthy.

460
00:29:50,150 --> 00:29:54,070
No, your food is the tastiest to me.

461
00:29:54,070 --> 00:29:57,250
Gosh, I know you're lying,

462
00:29:57,250 --> 00:29:59,660
but I appreciate it.

463
00:29:59,660 --> 00:30:01,040
Have some. Have some.

464
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:03,470
Hey, go get some scorched rice water.

465
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:06,310
Why are we having that before eating?

466
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:09,700
Just bring it if I said so. Stop arguing.

467
00:30:11,330 --> 00:30:13,040
Have some, have some.

468
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:14,590
Gosh, seriously.

469
00:30:14,590 --> 00:30:17,670
Don't say silly things for no reason.

470
00:30:19,090 --> 00:30:21,930
And the galbijjim. Leave some for me.

471
00:30:24,230 --> 00:30:27,100
 Did I upset you 

472
00:30:27,100 --> 00:30:31,190
 about something while you were here? 

473
00:30:31,190 --> 00:30:34,220
No, Ma'am! Why do you ask me that? Nothing like that at all.

474
00:30:34,220 --> 00:30:37,710
You treated me so well while I was here.

475
00:30:38,610 --> 00:30:43,080
Would you be able...

476
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:46,590
to tutor Lee Chan again, then?

477
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:50,990
Gosh, sit comfortably.

478
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:53,890
You probably don't know,

479
00:30:53,890 --> 00:30:59,700
but he's grown up a lot ever since he met you.

480
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:06,000
He quit his part-time job that I used to beg him to quit, which he scoffed at.

481
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,900
He sneaks into the storage room at night

482
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:12,850
to study math and English, too.

483
00:31:12,850 --> 00:31:16,290
He was trying to impress you, you know.

484
00:31:17,420 --> 00:31:23,490
But since you left, he seems to have lost focus.

485
00:31:23,490 --> 00:31:28,480
He said he would study for an exam at Ma Joo's house a few days ago

486
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:30,530
and he didn't even come home.

487
00:31:30,530 --> 00:31:33,750
But gosh, study, my foot.

488
00:31:33,750 --> 00:31:37,920
He came back with a bunch of bruises on his face.

489
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:40,810
 Did you have to ditch Lee Chan? You bastard. 

490
00:31:40,810 --> 00:31:42,560
 While handing out flyers looking for you, 

491
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:44,580
 he got punched in the face, cracked his head, and was hospitalized. 

492
00:31:44,580 --> 00:31:48,040
I couldn't even ask him if he had a fight or something.

493
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:51,340
I didn't want him to end up like his dad.

494
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:54,360
What about his father?

495
00:31:57,420 --> 00:32:01,460
His father got into gambling

496
00:32:01,460 --> 00:32:05,250
and he swung his fists at me,

497
00:32:05,250 --> 00:32:08,030
demanding money all the time.

498
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:16,770
 So, please, 

499
00:32:16,770 --> 00:32:20,010
 teach Lee Chan again, Teacher. 

500
00:32:22,340 --> 00:32:27,130
I can't pay you as much as that family, but I won't disappoint you.

501
00:32:29,750 --> 00:32:34,770
Ma'am, I don't live there because they pay me a lot.

502
00:32:34,770 --> 00:32:37,180
Why do you, then...

503
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:39,910
There's something I have to do there.

504
00:32:39,910 --> 00:32:42,580
But it's good for Lee Chan as well.

505
00:32:42,580 --> 00:32:47,490
Instead, I promise I'll come back when I'm done there.

506
00:32:57,080 --> 00:32:58,930
Go inside. I can go alone.

507
00:32:58,930 --> 00:33:00,350
Let's just go quietly.

508
00:33:00,350 --> 00:33:02,650
Grandma will yell at me, otherwise.

509
00:33:02,650 --> 00:33:05,980
Huh? Someone fixed this.

510
00:33:08,780 --> 00:33:10,760
Wait for me.

511
00:33:11,890 --> 00:33:15,690
You didn't actually fight someone, right?

512
00:33:15,690 --> 00:33:19,340
They didn't deserve fighting. I didn't.

513
00:33:19,340 --> 00:33:23,260
Se Kyeong said you fought because of me. Is that true?

514
00:33:23,260 --> 00:33:26,950
It wasn't because of you. I just had bad luck.

515
00:33:26,950 --> 00:33:29,300
How about you getting hospitalized?

516
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:32,860
Were you hiding at Ma Joo's so Grandmother wouldn't worry?

517
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:35,440
I heard the hospital food is good. So, I stayed briefly.

518
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:37,290
Were you really hospitalized, then?

519
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:40,000
How much did you get hurt, anyway?

520
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,810
Gosh, why are you overreacting so much?

521
00:33:41,810 --> 00:33:43,190
I'm fine, as you can see.

522
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:45,700
How about your ears? Did you hurt your ears? Can you hear well?

523
00:33:45,700 --> 00:33:48,900
I hear so well. It's too noisy, in fact.

524
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:52,600
Geez. Why did you disappear if you were so worried?

525
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:53,940
Anyway.

526
00:33:53,940 --> 00:33:58,080
Thank Yoon Cheong Ah for me when you get home.

527
00:33:58,080 --> 00:33:59,240
You know her?

528
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:02,390
Not well. I think she's Se Kyeong's friend.

529
00:34:02,390 --> 00:34:04,260
Anyway, thank her for me.

530
00:34:04,260 --> 00:34:05,840
She saved my life.

531
00:34:05,840 --> 00:34:08,790
Cheong Ah saved your life? How?

532
00:34:08,790 --> 00:34:10,600
Ask her yourself.

533
00:34:10,600 --> 00:34:12,360
I don't remember.

534
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:16,060
I went to her house to thank her and ask her about it, but they wouldn't let me in.

535
00:34:16,060 --> 00:34:20,220
How did you know she saved your life, then?

536
00:34:20,220 --> 00:34:22,610
Se Kyeong told me.

537
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:25,870
It's Ma Joo. See you then.

538
00:34:25,870 --> 00:34:28,570
You can come with me and thank Cheong Ah yourself—

539
00:34:28,570 --> 00:34:30,520
Later. He said, "Hurry."

540
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:33,800
We're rearranging the tracklist. Bye.

541
00:34:34,410 --> 00:34:37,620
You're dead if you're late to practice.

542
00:34:37,620 --> 00:34:39,900
You're dead if you see Se Kyeong behind my back, too.

543
00:34:39,900 --> 00:34:43,820
Whether we made a deal or not, we're finished, then. You know. Right?

544
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:48,780
 Dad got injured because of me. 

545
00:34:52,180 --> 00:34:57,210
 As a result, Mom ended up saving his life. 

546
00:34:57,210 --> 00:35:00,530
 How did you and Mom first meet? 

547
00:35:04,710 --> 00:35:09,260
 At a sign language class at the Association of the Deaf when I was 20. 

548
00:35:09,260 --> 00:35:11,150
 I went to learn sign language 

549
00:35:11,150 --> 00:35:13,910
 and fell in love with her at first sight. 

550
00:35:13,910 --> 00:35:17,350
 Dad didn't know Mom when he was 18. 

551
00:35:17,350 --> 00:35:19,970
 But now he knows her. 

552
00:35:25,270 --> 00:35:28,860
 Mom, who had a crush on him at age 18, 

553
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:31,490
 has a connection to him now. 

554
00:35:32,810 --> 00:35:34,540
 It's me. 

555
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:39,630
 I'm the one who connected Mom and Dad when they were 18. 

556
00:35:39,630 --> 00:35:40,810
 And... 

557
00:35:40,810 --> 00:35:43,040
 What if we don't see her at all? 

558
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:47,730
 Neither of us will see Choi Se Kyeong until the festival. That's fair. 

559
00:35:47,730 --> 00:35:49,520
 Deal! 

560
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,310
 The opportunity came just in time. 

561
00:35:57,900 --> 00:36:01,800
 The obstacle, Choi Se Kyeong, is gone. I can't waste this opportunity. 

562
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:04,550
 I should set Mom and Dad up before the festival, 

563
00:36:04,550 --> 00:36:07,240
 find out when Dad gets into the accident, 

564
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:10,350
 and prevent it from happening, no matter what. 

