00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:36,230
♫  The same way, the same way  ♫

581
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:41,730
Se Kyeong!

582
00:37:41,730 --> 00:37:43,410
Choi Se Kyeong!

583
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:46,210
Hey.

584
00:37:46,210 --> 00:37:48,250
How could you? I'm so sad!

585
00:37:48,250 --> 00:37:51,360
How could you not even call me when you're back in Korea?

586
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:54,290
I'm sorry, but who are you—

587
00:37:54,290 --> 00:37:55,920
Who am I?

588
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:58,160
You really don't know who I am?

589
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:01,510
 Damn it. I might get caught on my first day. 

590
00:38:01,510 --> 00:38:05,400
 Hey, it's me. Yoon Sang Ah from Seowon Arts High School. 

591
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:08,490
 Yoon Sang Ah, the daughter of the owner of Jinsung Instruments. 

592
00:38:09,290 --> 00:38:11,420
 I heard you came back to Korea. 

593
00:38:11,420 --> 00:38:14,010
 It was really true. 

594
00:38:15,350 --> 00:38:18,480
 My goodness. Is she your daughter? 

595
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:20,800
 Hi. 

596
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:25,010
 She looks exactly like when you were in high school. 

597
00:38:25,010 --> 00:38:28,610
 Shit, that clueless and chatty lady? 

598
00:38:28,610 --> 00:38:30,810
You're making me tear up.

599
00:38:30,810 --> 00:38:33,720
Hey, I was just joking.

600
00:38:33,720 --> 00:38:37,900
How could I not know Yoon Sang Ah, the daughter of Jinsung Instruments?

601
00:38:37,900 --> 00:38:39,950
Have you been well, Sang Ah?

602
00:38:39,950 --> 00:38:41,920
Whatever, girl!

603
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:44,710
You didn't miss me at all, did you?

604
00:38:44,710 --> 00:38:46,670
You wouldn't write me back, either.

605
00:38:46,670 --> 00:38:49,020
And you didn't even page me when you came back.

606
00:38:49,020 --> 00:38:50,770
You're so coldhearted.

607
00:38:50,770 --> 00:38:52,500
Are we really best friends?

608
00:38:52,500 --> 00:38:54,810
Hold on, hold on, hold on. Time. Time.

609
00:38:54,810 --> 00:38:57,650
You're my best friend? Not Yoon Cheong Ah?

610
00:38:57,650 --> 00:38:59,530
Hey!

611
00:39:11,450 --> 00:39:13,740
 I'll go to the teachers' office real quick. 

612
00:39:13,740 --> 00:39:16,410
 I think I'll get punished for what happened recently. 

613
00:39:16,410 --> 00:39:20,460
 Nothing will happen. Don't worry so much. 

614
00:39:27,500 --> 00:39:30,900
 Don't report everything to me. It's annoying. 

615
00:39:53,420 --> 00:39:55,470
 I know why you're angry. 

616
00:39:55,470 --> 00:39:57,010
 I'll help you. 

617
00:39:57,010 --> 00:39:58,930
 So please stop being angry at me. 

618
00:39:58,930 --> 00:40:01,430
 I'm always on your side. 

619
00:40:06,760 --> 00:40:09,710
What did you want to check with Cheong Ah, anyway?

620
00:40:09,710 --> 00:40:11,640
I'm your best friend, I said.

621
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:14,610
 What? Why is Choi Se Kyeong at school at this hour? 

622
00:40:14,610 --> 00:40:17,070
Does she also know you're back in school?

623
00:40:17,070 --> 00:40:20,290
 What? She's back in school? 

624
00:40:21,390 --> 00:40:22,810
 What do I do? 

625
00:40:22,810 --> 00:40:24,240
 Should I say hi since she saw me? 

626
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:26,300
 You're dead if you see Se Kyeong behind my back, too. 

627
00:40:26,300 --> 00:40:29,960
 Whether we made a deal or not, we're finished, then. You know, right? 

628
00:40:42,370 --> 00:40:43,690
 I'm sorry, Ahjumma. 

629
00:40:43,690 --> 00:40:45,340
 Forgive me. 

630
00:40:45,340 --> 00:40:46,550
That Shiba-sky.

631
00:40:46,550 --> 00:40:48,480
Hey, stop right there!

632
00:40:52,970 --> 00:40:55,070
You Shiba-sky.

633
00:40:59,100 --> 00:41:00,770
Move! Move!

634
00:41:05,390 --> 00:41:07,070
Hey, Ha Lee Chan.

635
00:41:09,340 --> 00:41:10,940
You won't fall that way.

636
00:41:10,940 --> 00:41:12,310
Hey, there's bad news.

637
00:41:12,310 --> 00:41:15,410
I just checked the voicemail from Yong Joon Gi.

638
00:41:15,410 --> 00:41:17,760
Choi Se Kyeong is back at school starting today.

639
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:19,430
- So what? 
 - What?

640
00:41:19,430 --> 00:41:21,010
- What? 
 - Yes.

641
00:41:21,010 --> 00:41:24,940
That means she'd see Ha Eun Gyeol at school every day.

642
00:41:24,940 --> 00:41:29,280
Yes! They're apparently chasing each other already.

643
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:31,100
Ha Eun Gyeol, son of a bitch.

644
00:41:31,100 --> 00:41:34,700
- He knew everything from the beginning. 
 - Hey, where are you going?

645
00:41:34,700 --> 00:41:36,450
I have no other solution.

646
00:41:36,450 --> 00:41:38,900
I just need to become cool.

647
00:41:38,900 --> 00:41:42,840
This means practice is the only way to survive.

648
00:41:44,140 --> 00:41:46,020
Come at me!

649
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:49,980
What?

650
00:41:52,810 --> 00:41:54,540
What's this?

651
00:41:56,160 --> 00:41:58,300
What are you doing in our room right now?

652
00:41:58,300 --> 00:42:01,590
What are you saying? Didn't the teacher tell you?

653
00:42:01,590 --> 00:42:04,410
We're using this room starting today.

654
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:11,090
 Hello. 

655
00:42:11,090 --> 00:42:12,990
Hold on! Hold on!

656
00:42:12,990 --> 00:42:14,900
Hold on!

657
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:18,110
Sir, you didn't tell me that last time.

658
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:19,170
I told you.

659
00:42:19,170 --> 00:42:21,330
It was the disciplinary committee's decision. What can I do?

660
00:42:21,330 --> 00:42:23,540
But you can't take our room away.

661
00:42:23,540 --> 00:42:25,480
You're telling us to disband.

662
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:27,880
Bingo. I'd be thankful if you do that.

663
00:42:27,880 --> 00:42:30,740
Don't go. No, don't go.

664
00:42:30,740 --> 00:42:32,000
Give us the room back.

665
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:33,970
You little— Let go of me.

666
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:36,820
- You'll rip my pants, you bastard! 
 - No, no, no.

667
00:42:36,820 --> 00:42:40,210
The festival is just around the corner. This is unfair.

668
00:42:40,210 --> 00:42:42,500
Just walk over me instead.

669
00:42:42,500 --> 00:42:44,020
Say one more word.

670
00:42:44,020 --> 00:42:46,930
I might not let you perform at the festival.

671
00:42:46,930 --> 00:42:48,780
No!

672
00:42:48,780 --> 00:42:50,580
Please! No!

673
00:42:50,580 --> 00:42:52,310
Gosh, Sir!

674
00:42:59,370 --> 00:43:02,710
Looks like we're not meant to be in a band.

675
00:43:10,100 --> 00:43:13,460
Who the hell is humming?

676
00:43:15,250 --> 00:43:17,260
Gosh.

677
00:43:17,260 --> 00:43:19,000
What can we do?

678
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:21,100
My motel closed down.

679
00:43:21,100 --> 00:43:23,370
I should find another place to stay.

680
00:43:23,370 --> 00:43:25,580
Are you serious right now?

681
00:43:25,580 --> 00:43:27,590
I can't unfurl my eyebrows listening to you.

682
00:43:27,590 --> 00:43:31,070
You should follow me if you guys are interested.

683
00:43:31,070 --> 00:43:34,950
There's always a hidden treasure where you fall.

684
00:43:38,030 --> 00:43:40,220
Let's go find treasure together.

685
00:43:41,930 --> 00:43:45,180
 Write a letter of apology and do on-campus volunteer for a week starting today. 

686
00:43:45,180 --> 00:43:48,380
 This is instead of getting suspended. So, be thankful. 

687
00:44:02,680 --> 00:44:04,720
Hey, stop right there!

688
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:06,700
- Bye. 
 - Hey!

689
00:44:06,700 --> 00:44:08,830
What are you two doing—

690
00:44:08,830 --> 00:44:11,380
   

691
00:44:11,380 --> 00:44:14,310
That little. Hey!

692
00:44:14,310 --> 00:44:16,150
Hey, Ha Eun Gyeol!

693
00:44:17,730 --> 00:44:20,050
Were they slave hunters in their previous lives?

694
00:44:20,050 --> 00:44:23,930
They chase each other whenever they make eye contact.

695
00:44:26,330 --> 00:44:29,290
How romantic.

696
00:44:29,290 --> 00:44:31,730
You'd better not get caught.

697
00:44:31,730 --> 00:44:33,230
Hey!

698
00:44:36,650 --> 00:44:39,250
- Hey, give me. 
 - You can't do that!

699
00:44:39,250 --> 00:44:40,970
Are you sure it's romantic?

700
00:44:40,970 --> 00:44:43,160
He might get killed if he's caught.

701
00:44:45,300 --> 00:44:48,530
What? What's that now?

702
00:45:02,580 --> 00:45:05,580
Get caught when I'm asking nicely.

703
00:45:05,580 --> 00:45:08,090
I'll kill you if you run again.

704
00:45:08,090 --> 00:45:09,480
Hey!

705
00:45:16,970 --> 00:45:19,110
You claimed me by publically confessing love to me.

706
00:45:19,110 --> 00:45:21,200
But now you abandon me by humiliating me?

707
00:45:21,200 --> 00:45:24,180
Am I a virus? Why avoid me? Why run away?

708
00:45:24,180 --> 00:45:26,310
I promised Lee Chan.

709
00:45:26,310 --> 00:45:29,450
That neither of us would see you to be fair.

710
00:45:29,450 --> 00:45:31,260
That's why you're avoiding me?

711
00:45:31,260 --> 00:45:33,100
- Until when? 
 - Until the festival.

712
00:45:33,100 --> 00:45:35,650
- When are you allowed to see me? 
 - After the festival.

713
00:45:35,650 --> 00:45:39,280
You bet your lives on the festival, didn't you?

714
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:42,750
Anyway, keep that in mind and try to cooperate.

715
00:45:42,750 --> 00:45:43,900
Cooperate, my foot.

716
00:45:43,900 --> 00:45:46,580
Am I your toy? How dare you play with me?

717
00:45:46,580 --> 00:45:49,110
- It's not that— 
 - Whatever.

718
00:45:49,110 --> 00:45:51,790
Anyway, it means the ball is in my court. Right?

719
00:45:51,790 --> 00:45:56,220
And I can decide how to play with that ball.

720
00:45:56,220 --> 00:45:57,800
How will you play with it?

721
00:45:57,800 --> 00:45:59,310
It's none of your business.

722
00:45:59,310 --> 00:46:02,000
Go now. You're free. Hoo!

723
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:07,680
I have a bad feeling.

724
00:46:07,680 --> 00:46:09,510
I have a bad feeling for some reason.

725
00:46:18,590 --> 00:46:20,050
 It's me. Ma Joo. 

726
00:46:20,050 --> 00:46:22,720
You can't tell anyone what I say to you now.

727
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:24,030
We lost the club room.

728
00:46:24,030 --> 00:46:25,950
 We'll practice in a new room from now on. 

729
00:46:25,950 --> 00:46:29,350
No one else can know the location except for the band members.

730
00:46:29,350 --> 00:46:30,680
 To keep it a secret, 

731
00:46:30,680 --> 00:46:33,910
non-members are not allowed. Keep that in mind.

732
00:46:51,050 --> 00:46:52,730
 I said I'll help you. Right? 

733
00:46:52,730 --> 00:46:55,210
 You need to come with me somewhere. 

734
00:46:57,770 --> 00:46:59,260
   

735
00:47:12,730 --> 00:47:14,680
 I know I'm cheating, 

736
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:17,660
 but I have to do this to set up Mom and Dad. 

737
00:47:19,130 --> 00:47:21,810
Seriously, I thought you were Lee Moon Se.

738
00:47:21,810 --> 00:47:25,170
Gosh, you're exaggerating.

739
00:47:25,170 --> 00:47:28,080
I tried depicting the fiery sunset in a red gradient.

740
00:47:28,080 --> 00:47:30,740
Did you catch that at all?

741
00:47:30,740 --> 00:47:32,250
Totally.

742
00:47:32,250 --> 00:47:36,070
I saw the sunset in front of my eyes. I thought there was blood everywhere.

743
00:47:36,070 --> 00:47:38,400
Gosh, you're the best.

744
00:47:39,110 --> 00:47:40,480
I'm sorry, Se Kyeong.

745
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:43,040
I wasted my talent because of someone.

746
00:47:43,040 --> 00:47:46,150
But I'll make sure to serenade you at the festival.

747
00:47:46,150 --> 00:47:47,920
 Serenade me? 

748
00:47:47,920 --> 00:47:50,120
Serenade... Seriously.

749
00:47:51,270 --> 00:47:53,840
What's going on right now?

750
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:55,370
- You came. 
 - Hey.

751
00:47:55,370 --> 00:47:58,880
I thought the location was a secret, and non-members weren't allowed.

752
00:47:58,880 --> 00:48:01,020
You shouldn't be saying that right now.

753
00:48:01,020 --> 00:48:03,450
- Come out. 
 - Gosh, so scary.

754
00:48:03,450 --> 00:48:05,990
If you're guilty, just apologize.

755
00:48:05,990 --> 00:48:07,800
Yet you're getting mad at me?

756
00:48:07,800 --> 00:48:09,740
- Come out. 
 - Let go!

757
00:48:09,740 --> 00:48:12,990
I'll go of my own volition...

758
00:48:15,640 --> 00:48:17,670
Go! Go!

759
00:48:18,580 --> 00:48:20,600
Here they go again.

760
00:48:20,600 --> 00:48:25,500
I feel like I'm on a swing bridge every day since I met them.

761
00:48:27,250 --> 00:48:28,800
Hi.

762
00:48:34,500 --> 00:48:36,220
 Sign language? 

763
00:48:41,870 --> 00:48:43,820
Hey, are you really going to do this?

764
00:48:43,820 --> 00:48:46,590
You promised not to see her before the festival.

765
00:48:46,590 --> 00:48:47,900
You're a cheater.

766
00:48:47,900 --> 00:48:50,170
You knew Se Kyeong was coming back to school when you said that.

767
00:48:50,170 --> 00:48:52,520
I told you many times that I didn't know.

768
00:48:52,520 --> 00:48:55,310
I jumped through hoops, trying to keep our promise.

769
00:48:55,310 --> 00:48:58,640
If you think jumping through hoops is unfair, just join the circus.

770
00:48:58,640 --> 00:49:00,560
Don't try to lie to me shamelessly.

771
00:49:00,560 --> 00:49:03,550
Wow, I'm about to go nuts here.

772
00:49:03,550 --> 00:49:06,250
Let's just forget about the promise, then.

773
00:49:06,250 --> 00:49:07,970
Can the frontman break the rule?

774
00:49:07,970 --> 00:49:10,780
You said it was a secret. You said no non-members are allowed.

775
00:49:10,780 --> 00:49:12,770
You brought a non-member, too.

776
00:49:12,770 --> 00:49:14,240
